# Final check for connectivity and density:
# - All major classes have multiple instances.
# - Instances are linked using various NORIA properties.
# - Agents, organizations, locations, product models are well-integrated.
# - Event records trigger trouble tickets, change requests impact resources/applications.
# - Observables are linked to network interfaces and resources.
# - Procedural elements are linked to dynamic elements.
# - KOS concepts are used for categorical properties.
# - Labels and comments are provided.
# - Syntax is Turtle.

# This graph is now quite dense and covers a good range of the NORIA vocabulary.
